{"word":"κακοήθης","slug":"κακοήθης","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κακοήθης</b></el> <el>(κᾰκο-ήθης, ες) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἦθος'><el>ἦθος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>ill-disposed, malicious</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a>, <el>τὸ κακόηθες</el> <i>wickedness, an ill habit</i> or <i>itch for doing</i> a thing, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of diseases, <i>malignant</i>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-θως</el>, <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}